instanceof -instanceof is a keyword used to check whether an object is an instance of a specific class or subclass. It's super handy for preventing ClassCastException errors!
classcastException -ClassCastException in Java happens when you try to cast an object to a class that it is not an instance of.

ClassCastException
When it happens: When you try to cast an object to an incompatible type
Type: Unchecked (Runtime exception)
Occurs at: Runtime

Example:

Object obj = "Hello";
Integer num = (Integer) obj; // ClassCastException
2. ClassNotFoundException
When it happens: When JVM cannot find a class during loading (usually with Class.forName())
Type: Checked exception
Occurs at: Compile-time requirement (must handle), but thrown at runtime

Example:

Class.forName("com.example.UnknownClass"); // ClassNotFoundException

| Feature  | ClassCastException   | ClassNotFoundException           |
| -------- | -------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| Cause    | Invalid type casting | Class not found in classpath     |
| Type     | Unchecked            | Checked                          |
| When     | Runtime              | During class loading             |
| Handling | Optional             | Must handle (try-catch / throws) |
