Java 17 features 
1. Sealed Classes (Standardized)
Restrict which classes can extend/implement a class
public sealed class Shape permits Circle, Rectangle {}

2. Pattern Matching for instanceof
No need for explicit casting
if (obj instanceof String s) {
    System.out.println(s.length());
}

3. Switch Enhancements (Preview → Improved)
More concise and powerful switch
String result = switch (day) {
    case MONDAY, FRIDAY -> "Work";
    default -> "Other";
};
4. Records (Standardized)
Concise way to create immutable data classes
public record Person(String name, int age) {}

👉 Automatically gives constructor, getters, toString(), etc.

5. Text Blocks (Standardized)
Multi-line strings
String json = """
    {
        "name": "Akhila"
    }
    """;
6. New Garbage Collectors
ZGC and Shenandoah improved (low latency)
7. Strong Encapsulation of JDK Internals
Internal APIs are strongly hidden (better security)
8. Deprecation & Removal
Removed old/unused APIs (like Applet API deprecated)
🔥 Quick Summary
Sealed classes → controlled inheritance
Records → less boilerplate
Pattern matching → cleaner code
Text blocks → readable strings
Better GC + performance
🧠 One-line interview answer:

“Java 17 introduced sealed classes, records, pattern matching for instanceof, text blocks, and improved performance with enhanced garbage collectors.”
